The paper discusses the use of bibliometric research evaluation, which is commonly used in computer science research. The focus of the paper is on proposing a multivariate stochastic model for measuring the performance of individual scientists, which could be relevant to several sub-categories such as cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computational Geometry), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
